Combine cucumbers, sour cream, dill, lemon juice and garlic; cover. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Cook and stir chicken in 2 tablespoons of the dressing in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned and cooked through. Remove from skillet; set aside. Add onions and remaining 2 tablespoons dressing to skillet; cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Return chicken to skillet; cook until heated through, stirring occasionally. Spoon chicken mixture evenly into pita bread halves. Serve topped with the cucumber mixture.